description: I received a bouquet of flowers (estimated value £25) from Oldham East & Saddleworth Liberal Democrats after being their guest speaker at the Annual Dinner on 14 October 2010,.  Address: Bank Gap, Carr Lane, Diggle, Oldham OL3 5ND.  Hours: 5 hrs. (Registered 10 November 2010)

5 September 2009, received Girlguiding Centenary merchandise: notebook (£2.50), pen (£1), pencil (£0.35), keyring (£2.60), and badge (£1.50), as a thank you for speaking at the Bishopbriggs Girlguiding Centenary celebrations. Address: 50 Brackenbrae Avenue, Bishopbriggs, G64.  Hours: 1hr.  (Registered 6 September 2009)

June 2010 received a bottle of wine (estimated value £5) as thanks for participating in a "question time" event for a local school run by Aviva as part of their citizenship programme. Address: Aviva, Cruan House, Westhill Road Bishopbriggs G64. Hours: 2hrs (Registered 7 June 2010)
30 July 2010 received a bunch of flowers (estimated value £10) for attending an evening at the Milngavie Youth Cafe, 26 Mugdock Road, Milngavie G62. Hours: 2hrs (Registered 7 June 2010)
